# type(scope): brief description
#
# Longer description if needed. Explain the "why", not the "what".
#
# Commit messages must follow Conventional Commits format:
# type(scope): description
#
# Types:
#   feat:     New feature
#   fix:      Bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation changes
#   style:    Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
#   refactor: Code refactoring
#   test:     Adding or updating tests
#   chore:    Maintenance tasks
#   perf:     Performance improvements
#   ci:       CI/CD changes
#   build:    Build system changes
#   revert:   Revert previous commit
#
# Examples:
#   feat(skyhook): add orbit mode for circular paths
#   fix(operator): resolve memory leak in message routing
#   docs(readme): update build instructions for ROS 2
#   chore(deps): update go dependencies
